The paper discusses self-organizing particle systems (SOPS) and their ability to form shapes through local control and movement. This topic falls under the category of multi-agent systems and robotics, which is covered by cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the computational elements and algorithms used in SOPS, which falls under the category of computer science theory, covered by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper discusses the self-organizing nature of SOPS, which falls under the category of control systems and optimization, covered by cs.SY (Systems and Control).
